1.I am not a Muslim, but I find this qawwali magically soothing; How devoted Mr. Aslam interprets the qawwali is simply awesome and fascinating. And I love this masterpiece even more after obtaining the English lyrics! Thank you Mr. Aslam! You have made the qawwali art more accessible to music lovers worldwide. 
2. Would someone kindly explain why it is not agreeable to call a qawwali "a song"? I am quite interested about this. Is it bcoz its holiness shouldn't be paralleled with a "song"? 
Greetings from Taiwan
